d of\nincreasing [K/Fe] with age is recognized for dwarfs, while any systematic\ntendency is not observed for Kepler giants. These consequences may suggest that\nevolution of [K/Fe] with time in the galactic disk does exist but proceeded\nmore gradually than previously thought, and its condition is appreciably\nlocation-dependent.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 14 Jan 2020 02:08:36 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-01-15"}
